  "title" : "How to format Joda-Time DateTime to only mm/dd/yyyy?",
  "body" : "<p>I have a string \"<code>11/15/2013 08:00:00</code>\", I want to format it to \"<code>11/15/2013</code>\", what is the correct <code>DateTimeFormatter</code> pattern?</p>\n\n<p>I've tried many and googled and still unable to find the correct pattern.</p>\n\n<p>edit: I am looking for <a href=\"http://www.joda.org/joda-time/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Joda-Time</a> <a href=\"http://www.joda.org/joda-time/apidocs/org/joda/time/format/DateTimeFormatter.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>DateTimeFormatter</code></a>, not Java's SimpleDateFormat..</p>\n"
